Macquarie Hires Two Former HSBC Wealth Advisers for Its Calgary Office

-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 
2011-08-23T17:12:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/macquarie-hires-two-former-hsbc-wealth-advisers-for-its-calgary-office.html
Macquarie Group Ltd. (MQG) ’s Canadian
private wealth unit hired former  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  financial
advisers Nick Twyman and Bryn Gardener-Evans.  The advisers have joined Macquarie’s Calgary office,
company spokesman Aaron Boles said today in a telephone
interview from Toronto. Macquarie has hired about 60 advisers
since buying Blackmont Capital from  CI Financial Corp. (CIX)  last
year, Boles said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sean B. Pasternak in Toronto at 
